.SS "int32_t adi_analog_calibrate (uint8_t port)"
Calibrates the analog sensor on the specified port and returns the new calibration value\&.

.PP
This method assumes that the true sensor value is not actively changing at this time and computes an average from approximately 500 samples, 1 ms apart, for a 0\&.5 s period of calibration\&. The average value thus calculated is returned and stored for later calls to the \fBadi_analog_read_calibrated()\fP and \fBadi_analog_read_calibrated_HR()\fP functions\&. These functions will return the difference between this value and the current sensor value when called\&.

.PP
Do not use this function when the sensor value might be unstable (gyro rotation, accelerometer movement)\&.

.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The ADI currently returns data at 10ms intervals, in constrast to the calibrate functionâ€™s 1ms sample rate\&.
.RE
.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port to calibrate (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H')
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The average sensor value computed by this function
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT 1

void initialize() {
  adi_analog_calibrate(ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT);
  printf("Calibrated Reading: %d\\n", adi_analog_read_calibrated(ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT));
  // All readings from then on will be calibrated
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_analog_read (uint8_t port)"
Gets the 12-bit value of the specified port\&.

.PP
The value returned is undefined if the analog pin has been switched to a different mode\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as an analog input

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H') for which the value will be returned
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The analog sensor value, where a value of 0 reflects an input voltage of nearly 0 V and a value of 4095 reflects an input voltage of nearly 5 V
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT 1

void opcontrol() {
  while (true) {
    printf("Sensor Reading: %d\\n", adi_analog_read(ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT));
    delay(5);
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_analog_read_calibrated (uint8_t port)"
Gets the 12 bit calibrated value of an analog input port\&.

.PP
The \fBadi_analog_calibrate()\fP function must be run first\&. This function is inappropriate for sensor values intended for integration, as round-off error can accumulate causing drift over time\&. Use \fBadi_analog_read_calibrated_HR()\fP instead\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as an analog input

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H') for which the value will be returned
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The difference of the sensor value from its calibrated default from -4095 to 4095
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT 1

void opcontrol() {
  while (true) {
    printf("Sensor Reading: %d\\n", adi_analog_read_calibrated(ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT));
    delay(5);
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_analog_read_calibrated_HR (uint8_t port)"
Gets the 16 bit calibrated value of an analog input port\&.

.PP
The \fBadi_analog_calibrate()\fP function must be run first\&. This is intended for integrated sensor values such as gyros and accelerometers to reduce drift due to round-off, and should not be used on a sensor such as a line tracker or potentiometer\&.

.PP
The value returned actually has 16 bits of "precision", even though the ADC only reads 12 bits, so that error induced by the average value being between two values when integrated over time is trivial\&. Think of the value as the true value times 16\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as an analog input

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H') for which the value will be returned
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The difference of the sensor value from its calibrated default from -16384 to 16384
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT 1

void opcontrol() {
  while (true) {
    adi_analog_calibrate(ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT);
    printf("Sensor Reading: %d\\n", adi_analog_read_calibrated_HR(ANALOG_SENSOR_PORT));
    delay(5);
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_digital_get_new_press (uint8_t port)"
Gets a rising-edge case for a digital button press\&.

.PP
This function is not thread-safe\&. Multiple tasks polling a single button may return different results under the same circumstances, so only one task should call this function for any given button\&. E\&.g\&., Task A calls this function for buttons 1 and 2\&. Task B may call this function for button 3, but should not for buttons 1 or 2\&. A typical use-case for this function is to call inside opcontrol to detect new button presses, and not in any other tasks\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as a digital input

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port to read (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H')
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
1 if the button is pressed and had not been pressed the last time this function was called, 0 otherwise\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define DIGITAL_SENSOR_PORT 1

void opcontrol() {
  while (true) {
    if (adi_digital_get_new_press(DIGITAL_SENSOR_PORT)) {
      // Toggle pneumatics or other state operations
    }
    delay(5);
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_digital_read (uint8_t port)"
Gets the digital value (1 or 0) of a port configured as a digital input\&.

.PP
If the port is configured as some other mode, the digital value which reflects the current state of the port is returned, which may or may not differ from the currently set value\&. The return value is undefined for ports configured as any mode other than a Digital Input\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as a digital input

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port to read (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H')
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
True if the pin is HIGH, or false if it is LOW
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define DIGITAL_SENSOR_PORT 1

void opcontrol() {
  while (true) {
    printf("Sensor Value: %d\\n", adi_digital_read(DIGITAL_SENSOR_PORT));
    delay(5);
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_digital_write (uint8_t port, bool value)"
Sets the digital value (1 or 0) of a port configured as a digital output\&.

.PP
If the port is configured as some other mode, behavior is undefined\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as a digital output

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIport\fP The ADI port to read (from 1-8, 'a'-'h', 'A'-'H') 
.br
\fIvalue\fP An expression evaluating to "true" or "false" to set the output to HIGH or LOW respectively, or the constants HIGH or LOW themselves
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
1 if the operation was successful or PROS_ERR if the operation failed, setting errno\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define DIGITAL_SENSOR_PORT

void opcontrol() {
  bool state = LOW;
  while (true) {
    state != state;
    adi_digital_write(DIGITAL_SENSOR_PORT, state);
    delay(5); // toggle the sensor value every 50ms
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
.SS "int32_t adi_encoder_get (\fBadi_encoder_t\fP enc)"
Gets the number of ticks recorded by the encoder\&.

.PP
There are 360 ticks in one revolution\&.

.PP
This function uses the following values of errno when an error state is reached: ENXIO - The given value is not within the range of ADI Ports EADDRINUSE - The port is not configured as an encoder

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIenc\fP The \fBadi_encoder_t\fP object from \fBadi_encoder_init()\fP to read
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The signed and cumulative number of counts since the last start or reset
.RE
.PP
\fBExample\fP 
.PP
.nf
#define PORT_TOP 1
#define PORT_BOTTOM 2

void opcontrol() {
  adi_encoder_t enc = adi_encoder_init(PORT_TOP, PORT_BOTTOM, false);
  while (true) {
  printf("Encoder Value: %d\\n", adi_encoder_get(enc));
  delay(5);
  }
}

.fi
.PP
 
